<1ST_LINE>r a AM-BRF--DrugSting     05-22 0143</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Drug Sting,0146</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Sheriff's Department Nets An Estimated $80,000 In Drug Sting</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CLEVELAND, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sheriff's deputies seized an estimated
$80,000 in cocaine, marijuana and vehicles to cap a 10-month
undercover investigation into drug trafficking, an official said
Saturday.
   ``We had decided that we had already lost the war against drugs,
but we were going to win a few battles along the way,'' said
Detective Barry Tharp, of the Bradley County Sheriff's department's
criminal investigation division.
   At least 45 people were arrested late Friday and early Saturday.
Officers hoped to arrest 40 more on charges of selling and
delivering cocaine, marijuana and LSD, Tharp said.
   ``We've got a drug problem here, but we didn't expect it to be
this many people,'' he said. ``There's no way to eradicate drugs,
but we are trying to get what we can along the way.''
</TEXT>
