<1ST_LINE>r i AM-FerryBrawl     05-22 0160</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Ferry Brawl,0163</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Fight Aboard Ferry Forces Return To Port</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHERBOURG, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A brawl broke out on a ferry crossing
the English Channel, and the crew was forced to return to port at
Cherbourg where 13 young British men were arrested, French
immigration police said Sunday.
   About 30 people began fighting shortly after the P and O ferry
Viking Voyager left Cherbourg on Saturday night for Portsmouth,
England, said a police spokesman, speaking on condition of
anonymity.
   When crew members were unable to control the fight, the captain
returned to Cherbourg and asked immigration police to board his
ship and take off 13 men described as ``hooligans.''
   The 13 were led in handcuffs to police headquarters and
released. Because the brawl took place at sea aboard a ship
registered in Britain, any charges will have to be pressed by
British authorities, the French police said.
   No injuries were reported. It was not known what sparked the
fight.
</TEXT>
