<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF-TugSinks     05-22 0153</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF-Tug Sinks,0156</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Ship Hits Tug; Five Pulled From Harbor Waters</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A container ship ran across the bow of a tugboat
near the Verrazano-Narrows Bridge on Sunday, dumping the tug's crew
of five into the water and sending the vessel to the bottom,
authorities said.
   The crewmen were pulled quickly from the chilly water by workers
on a nearby tug that rushed to the scene.
   One victim had a broken ankle and another suffered a head injury
in the collision, according to Coast Guard Warrant Officer Fred
Schlager. No other serious injuries were reported.
   The 110-foot tug Elizabeth Moran was pushing a cement barge
through the harbor when it was hit by the Figaroa, a 650-foot car
carrier en route to Port Elizabeth in New Jersey, the Coast Guard
said.
   Visibility was very low in the area of the bridge, which
connects Brooklyn and Staten Island, authorities said.
 
