<2ND_LINE>PM-Gas Prices,0123</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Gas Prices Remain Steady</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: This is for Monday PMs.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Retail gas prices nationwide remained steady
over the past two weeks, according to a survey of about 12,000
service stations.
   The average national price for a gallon of gasoline on May 20
was 100.26 cents, just three-hundredths of a penny less than the
average for May 6, said Trilby Lundberg, who oversees the
twice-monthly Lundberg Survey of gas prices.
   Prices at self-serve stations, according to the survey were:
regular unleaded, 91.33; premium unleaded,1.0588; regular leaded
88.53.
   Prices for full service stations, which account for about
one-fifth of retail gasoline business, were: regular unleaded
1.1963; premium unleaded 1.2969; regular leaded, 1.1538.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
